body.p:
Several studies highlighted that A. baumannii is able to express several virulence factors, including those required for biofilm formation, desiccation resistance, secretion systems, micronutrient acquisition systems, and twitching motility, as well as adherence to and invasion of human epithelial cells in vitro and in vivo (I draw you attention to some as follows: https://doi.org/10.1128/mSystems.00604-20;
https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijid.2020.09.352;
https://doi.org/10.1038/ncomms13414;
https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-21841-9;
https://doi.org/10.1128/mBio.02193-16).
